\begin_layout Subsection*
Version 0.41
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Reverted part of release 0.40 such that images are back to using absolute
 urls.
 This is because Wordpress depends on absolute url references so that whether
 you've viewing the index view or an individual post view, it still knows
 where to find the image.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Version 0.40 (May 19, 2012)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
src attributes for images are now relative, such that if you move your blog
 from one domain to another, the images will still show up.
 (This was later reverted in 0.41)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Generated by eLyXer
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, which is normally wrapped in a div with an id of 'footer', is now wrapped
 in a div of class 'generated_by_elyxer' (since wordpress strips out all
 id's upon upload), for easier css suppression without conflicting names.
 
\end_layout

